{{sport-year-stub}}

The '''2013 French Road Cycling Cup''' was the 22nd edition of the [[French Road Cycling Cup]].

Compared to the previous edition, the [[Flèche d'Emeraude]] was replaced by the [[Tour de la Somme]]. The defending champion from [[2012 French Road Cycling Cup|2012]] was [[Samuel Dumoulin]], who won for a second consecutive time after a third place in the final event allowed him to overtake [[Bryan Coquard]] and [[Anthony Geslin]] in the overall standings. [[Bryan Coquard]] still won the youth classification, while {{ct|FDJ|2013b}} won the teams competition.

