{{Infobox international football competition | tourney_name = UEFA European Under-17 Championship | year = 2020 | other_titles = <!--Tournament name in native language of hosts--> Jalgpalli alla 19-aastaste Euroopa meistrivõistlused 2020 | image = <!--Tournament logo--> | size = | caption = | country = Estonia | dates = May 2020 | num_teams = 16 | confederations = 1 | venues = TBD | cities = TBD | champion_other = <!--{{fbu|17|}}--> | count = | second_other = <!--{{fbu|17|}}--> | matches = | goals = | attendance = | top_scorer = | player = | prevseason = [[2019 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|2019]] | nextseason = [[2021 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|2021]] }} The '''2020 UEFA European Under-17 Championship''' (also known as '''UEFA Under-17 Euro 2020''') will be the 19th edition of the [[UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] (38th edition if the Under-16 era is also included), the annual international youth [[association football|football]] championship organised by [[UEFA]] for the men's under-17 national teams of Europe. [[Estonia]], which were selected by UEFA on 9 December 2016, will host the tournament.<ref name="hosts">{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/news/newsid=2429056.html|title=Ireland, Estonia given U17 honours for 2019, 2020|publisher=UEFA|date=9 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.baltic-course.com/eng/baltic_news/?doc=17416|title=Estonia to host U-17 European Football Championship final in 2020|last=курс|first=The Baltic Course - Балтийский|work=The Baltic Course {{!}} Baltic States news & analytics|access-date=2018-01-18}}</ref>
A total of 16 teams will play in the tournament, with players born on or after 1 January 2003 eligible to participate.
==Qualification== {{main|2020 UEFA European Under-17 Championship qualification}}
All 55 UEFA nations entered the competition, and with the hosts Estonia qualifying automatically, the other 54 teams will compete in the qualifying competition to determine the remaining 15 spots in the final tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/news/newsid=2583417.html|title=2019/20 U17 qualifying round draw seedings|publisher=UEFA|date=23 November 2018}}</ref> The qualifying competition consists of two rounds: '''Qualifying round''', which takes place in autumn 2019, and '''Elite round''', which takes place in spring 2020.
===Qualified teams=== The following teams qualified for the final tournament.
