{{Primary sources|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox sport governing body | name = Basketball Federation of India | abbrev = BFI | logo = | logosize = 160 | sport = [[Basketball]] | category = | image = | caption = | jurisdiction = [[India]] | founded = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1950}} | aff = [[FIBA]] | region = [[FIBA Asia]] | regionyear = | headquarters = [[New Delhi]] | location = | president = K. Govindraj | chairman = | chairperson = | chiefexec = | vicepresident = Teja Singh Dhaliwal | director = | secretary = Chander Mukhi Sharma | coach = Philip John Weber | womenscoach = | key staff = | operating income = | sponsor = | year closed = | replaced = | prevfounded = | url = http://www.basketballfederationindia.org/ | countryflag = India }} '''Basketball Federation of India''' ('''BFI''') is the governing and controlling body of [[Basketball in India]]. It is responsible for the development and promotion of the sport at all levels. BFI manages all the national level basketball operations in India. It is involved in organizing training camps and national tournaments, and in preparing Indian teams for both men and women international competitions in various age categories. The national team of India is also called as '''Young Cagers'''.<ref name=aboutBFI>{{cite web | url = http://www.indiabasketball.org/inner.php?page=13 | title = About the BFI | publisher = BFI | accessdate = {{date|30 January 2013|dmy}} }}</ref>
==History== First national level tournaments were organized in India in 1934.<ref name=aboutBFI/> The [[India national basketball team]] became a member of [[FIBA]] in 1936.<ref name=aboutBFI/> The governing body, BFI, was formed in 1950.<ref name=aboutBFI/> [[Poonam Mahajan]] is the President (and also the first women President) of Basketball Federation of India.<ref>[http://www.dnaindia.com/sport/report-poonam-mahajan-becomes-first-women-president-of-basketball-federation-of-india-2072735 Poonam Mahajan becomes first women president of Basketball Federation of India]</ref> The current head of BFI is R.S. Gill.<ref name=aboutBFI/>
==Awards and recognition for Indian Basketball players== The Indian basketball players have also won several trophies for their country. There are 17 Indian basketball players, who have been honored by the [[Government of India]] through the [[Arjuna Award]].<ref name=BFIAwards>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiabasketball.org/inner.php?page=4 |accessdate=January 29, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130110095730/http://www.indiabasketball.org/inner.php?page=4 |archivedate=January 10, 2013 }}</ref> 2 players were bestowed with [[Dhyan Chand Award]]s for lifetime achievement.<ref name=BFIAwards/>
==See also== * [[Basketball in India]] * [[Sport in India|Sports in India]] * [[Arjuna Award#Arjun Awardees in Basketball|Arjun Awardees in Basketball]] * [[Dhyan Chand Award]]
