{{Infobox football biography |name = Dren Feka |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Dren Feka |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1997|6|9|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Bad Oldesloe]], [[Germany]] |height = {{convert|1.83|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} |position = [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|Defensive midfielder]] |currentclub = [[FC Luzern|Luzern]] |clubnumber = 36 |youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2009 |youthclubs1 = TSV Bargteheide |youthyears2 = 2009–2015 |youthclubs2 = [[Hamburger SV]] |years1 = 2015–2017 |clubs1 = [[Hamburger SV II]] |caps1 = 44 |goals1 = 3 |years2 = 2017– |clubs2 = [[FC Luzern|Luzern]] |caps2 = 3 |goals2 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2013 |nationalteam1 = [[Germany national under-16 football team|Germany U16]] |nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |nationalyears2 = 2013 |nationalteam2 = [[Albania national under-17 football team|Albania U17]] |nationalcaps2 = 3 |nationalgoals2 = 0 |nationalyears3 = 2013 |nationalteam3 = [[Germany national under-17 football team|Germany U17]] |nationalcaps3 = 2 |nationalgoals3 = 0 |nationalyears4 = 2015 |nationalteam4 = [[Germany national under-19 football team|Germany U19]] |nationalcaps4 = 2 |nationalgoals4 = 0 |nationalyears5 = 2017– |nationalteam5 = [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo U21]] |nationalcaps5 = 4 |nationalgoals5 = 0 <!-- Don't add parameter unless he debuted with national team. |nationalyears6 = 2018– |nationalteam6 = [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] |nationalcaps6 = 0 |nationalgoals6 = 0 --> |club-update = 28 October 2017 |nationalteam-update = 23 May 2018 }} '''Dren Feka''' (born 9 June 1997) is a [[Kosovo Albanian]] professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for Swiss club [[FC Luzern|Luzern]].
==Club career== <!---------------------------------- ===Early career=== {{Empty section|date=November 2017}} ----------------------------------->
===Luzern=== On 24 June 2017. Feka signed to [[Swiss Super League]] side [[FC Luzern|Luzern]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.luzernerzeitung.ch/sport/fussball/fcl/hsv-vermeldet-wechsel-von-dren-feka-zum-fc-luzern;art98,1052822|title=HSV vermeldet Wechsel von Dren Feka zum FC Luzern|language=German|publisher= [[Neue Luzerner Zeitung]]|date= 24 June 2017}}</ref> On 23 July 2017, he made his debut in a 1–0 home win against [[FC Lugano|Lugano]] after being named in the starting line-up.
==International career== <!---------------------------------- ===Germany=== ====Youth==== {{Empty section|date=November 2017}} ----------------------------------->
===Albania=== ====Under-17==== On 14 February 2013. Feka received a call-up from [[Albania national under-17 football team|Albania U17]] for the [[Exhibition game|friendly matches]] against [[Slovenia national under-17 football team|Slovenia U17]] and [[Kosovo national under-17 football team|Kosovo U17]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://asport.al/shqiperia-merr-talentin-e-hamburgut-leon-morina/|title=Shqipëria merr talentin e Hamburgut, Leon Morina|language=Albanian|website= aSport|date= 14 February 2013}}</ref> On 20 February 2013, he making his debut with Albania U17 in match against Slovenia U17 after being named in the starting line-up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportishqiptar.com.al/newsite/2013/02/20/kombetarja-u-17-barazon-ne-miqesoren-ndaj-sllovenise/|title=Kombëtarja U-17 barazon në miqësoren ndaj Sllovenisë|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Sporti Shqiptar]]|date=20 February 2013}}</ref>
===Kosovo=== ====Under-21==== On 6 November 2017. Feka received a call-up from [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo U21]] for a [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group 5|2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]] matches against [[Israel national under-21 football team|Israel U21]] and [[Azerbaijan national under-21 football team|Azerbaijan U21]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/?p=24057|title=Prekazi publikoi listën e futbollistëve për ndeshjet me Izraelin dhe Azerbejxhanin|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=6 November 2017}}</ref> On 9 November 2017, he made his debut with Kosovo U21 in match against Israel U21 after being named in the starting line-up.
====Senior==== On 23 May 2018. Feka received a call-up from [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] for a [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Albania national football team|Albania]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/2018/05/23/lista-e-futbollisteve-te-ftuar-per-miqesoret-me-shqiperine-dhe-bregun-e-fildishte/|title=Lista e futbollistëve të ftuar për miqësoret me Shqipërinë dhe Bregun e Fildishtë|quote=Initially, Bernard Challandes published the list of invited footballers for the friendlies with Albania and Ivory Coast, but the match against Ivory Coast was canceled. The canceled match was replaced with Iran that was also canceled|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|language=Albanian|date=23 May 2018}}</ref> he was an unused bench in that match.
