{{unreferenced|date=May 2015}} {{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Lampang Province Stadium | image = Pic lampangstadium.jpg | location = [[Lampang Province|Lampang]], [[Thailand]] | coordinates = {{coord|18.302664|99.473113|format=dms|type:landmark_scale:3000}} | opened = | owner = Lampang Provincial Administrative Organization | operator = Lampang Provincial Administrative Organization | surface = [[Grass]] | construction_cost = | former_names = | tenants = [[Lampang F.C.]] | seating_capacity = 5,500 }}
'''Lampang Province Stadium or Nong Kra Ting Stadium''' ({{lang-th|สนามกีฬาจังหวัดลําปาง หรือ สนามกีฬาหนองกระทิง}}) (known as '''Nong Krating Stadium''') is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Lampang Province]], [[Thailand]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Lampang F.C.|Lampang Football Club]]. The stadium holds 5,500 people.<ref>http://www.painaidii.com/business/115110/album/</ref><ref>https://th-th.facebook.com/LampangFootballclub/posts/%E0%B8%AA%E0%B8%99%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%B5%E0%B8%AC%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%88%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%A5%E0%B8%B3%E0%B8%9B%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%99%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%B0%E0%B8%97%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%87-%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%87%E0%B9%80%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%A2%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%82%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87-%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%96%E0%B8%A1%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A1%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%95-%E0%B8%A5%E0%B8%B3%E0%B8%9B%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%87-%E0%B9%80%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%9F%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%B5-%E0%B8%95%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%94-%E0%B8%97%E0%B9%87%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%9B-5-%E0%B8%AA%E0%B8%99%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A1/1193679670745912/</ref> ==References== <references/>
{{coord|18.302664|99.473113|type:landmark_region:TH|display=title}}
[[Category:Multi-purpose stadiums in Thailand]] [[Category:Buildings and structures in Lampang Province]]
{{Thailand-sports-venue-stub}}

'''Lithuania National Stadium''' is a new multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Vilnius]], [[Lithuania]], that is under construction since 1987. It will be used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and will host the home matches of the [[Lithuania national football team]]. The stadium will have a capacity of 25,000 people. It would replace the use of [[S. Darius and S. Girėnas Stadium]], [[Žalgiris Stadium]], and [[LFF Stadium]]. The construction was temporarily abandoned since March 2010. The minister of interior, Dailis Alfonsas Barakauskas, has said that it was expected to be finished by 2016 to a cost around [[LTL]] 260 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vilnius: Construction of national stadium to restart one more time|url=http://stadiumdb.com/news/2013/05/vilnius_construction_of_national_stadium_to_restart_one_more_time|website=stadiumdb.com|accessdate=31 January 2018|date=22 May 2013}}</ref>
Stadium construction was revitalized in early 2016. It was planned to be completed between 2019 and 2020 at the cost of about [[EUR]] 80–100 million.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gudavičius|first1=Stasys|title=Valstybės šimtmečiui nespės: Nacionalinio stadiono finišas ir vėl atidedamas|url=http://www.vz.lt/2016/04/22/valstybes-simtmeciui-nespes-nacionalinio-stadiono-finisas-ir-vel-atidedamas|website=vz.lt|accessdate=31 January 2018|language=lt-LT|date=22 April 2016}}</ref> However, the construction was not continued and a new competition for the building of the stadium was announced in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Finišo tiesioji dėl nacionalinio stadiono Vilniuje: yra du projektai|url=https://www.15min.lt/verslas/naujiena/kvadratinis-metras/nekilnojamasis-turtas/finiso-tiesioji-del-nacionalinio-stadiono-vilniuje-bent-vienas-projektas-tikrai-yra-973-893862|website=15min.lt|accessdate=31 January 2018|language=lt-LT|date=8 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Samkus|first1=Mindaugas|title=Nacionalinis stadionas: svarbiausios datos|url=https://www.15min.lt/verslas/naujiena/kvadratinis-metras/nekilnojamasis-turtas/nacionalinis-stadionas-svarbiausios-datos-973-919144|website=15min.lt|accessdate=31 January 2018|language=lt-LT|date=31 January 2018}}</ref>
